<text id="A7152T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>A request for books ("Colburns First Lessons in Intellecual Arith," "Greenleafs primary," etc.).</p> 
</div1> 
 
</front> 

<body id="d4">
<div1 type="letter" id="d5">
<head>
<name type="recipient">Rev E P Smith</name> 
<name type="place">Staunton Va</name> 
</head>

<opener>
<dateline>
    <date value="1869-03-12">Mar 12/69</date> 
</dateline> 
<salute>Dear Sir</salute> 
</opener> 

<p>The Colburns First Lessons in Intellecual Arith 23 copies at 30 ea I return to you by express this morning--as they are rather difficult for the pupils for whom they were intended and Miss Burke does not like them on that account</p>
	<p>I want some mental arith that contains the <hi rend="underline">Multiplication Table</hi> as one of the principle things and also the ordinary Tables of <hi rend="underline">weights and measures</hi></p>
	<p>Greenleafs primary I think is such  I know Greenleaf has one but it may not be called <hi rend="underline">Primary</hi>  Please send by express 4 <del rend="none" hand="h1"></del> of uniform kind with<pb n="2"/> multiplication table in it or a few little cards with the table but, the Books are better</p>
	<p>I am sorry to trouble you but the books are important to the school</p>


<closer>
<salute>Very Respectfully</salute> 
<signed>John Scott</signed> 

<name type="place">New York</name> 
</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
</text> 
